  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HR Executive (F&B Recruitment)",
  "description": "<p><strong>❗Current work location @ Shun Li Industrial Complex❗</strong><br /><strong>❗New office @ Senoko Way in Q2 2026❗</strong><br /></p><p></p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li>Manage full-cycle recruitment for F&B retail crew</li><li>Partner with operations leaders to understand staffing needs and workforce planning</li><li>Source candidates through job portals, social media, referrals, and industry networks</li><li>Screen, interview, and assess candidates to ensure cultural and operational fit</li><li>Coordinate and execute interviews, offers, and onboarding processes</li><li>Build and maintain a strong talent pipeline for current and future openings</li><li>Track recruitment metrics and continuously improve hiring processes</li><li>Support employer branding initiatives within the F&B talent market</li><li>Conduct exit interviews and track resignation trends.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Employee Engagement & HR Operations</strong></p><ul><li>Support HR programs including welfare initiatives, staff events, and recognition programs</li><li>Conduct outlet visits to understand staff morale and working conditions</li><li>Assist in grievance handling and follow up on employee concerns</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>HR Administration & Generalist Support</strong></p><ul><li>Maintain and update employee records in the HRIS system</li><li>Assist in processing documentation for work passes</li><li>Support payroll in staff attendance and leave administration</li><li>Ensure compliance with local employment laws and company policies</li></ul><p><br /></p><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li>Proven experience in talent acquisition or recruitment, preferably within the F&B, hospitality, or retail industry</li><li>Strong understanding of high-volume and operational hiring</li><li>Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills</li><li>Ability to work in a fast-paced, hands-on environment</li><li>Familiarity with recruitment platforms</li><li>Diploma or degree in Human Resources, Business, or a related field (preferred)</li></ul>",
